🔐 1. What Is Entra ID Protection? (Simple Definition)
Microsoft Entra ID Protection is a cloud-native identity threat detection system that analyzes:

Users
Sign-ins
Sessions
Credentials
Behavior
Threat intelligence

And assigns risk levels to them.
According to Microsoft Learn:

Entra ID Identity Protection uses machine learning and threat intelligence to detect risky users, risky sign-ins, and compromised credentials, and allows automated remediation using risk-based policies.
 [community....eworks.com]

Identity Protection is the core security brain of Entra ID.

