🧠 3. The Three Pillars of Identity Protection (Microsoft Learn)
Microsoft documents three core risk areas Identity Protection detects:
✔ 1. User Risk
Suspicious activity indicating the user account is compromised.
 [community....eworks.com]
✔ 2. Sign-in Risk
Suspicious patterns during sign-in (impossible travel, TOR, malware).
 [community....eworks.com]
✔ 3. Risky Users / Risky Credentials
Accounts that Microsoft believes attackers have control over.
 [community....eworks.com]
These risks feed directly into Conditional Access → allowing automated blocking & remediation.

