🛡 5. Risk-Based Conditional Access Policies
Identity Protection integrates directly with Conditional Access.
Microsoft Learn confirms:

Risk-based Conditional Access can automatically block high-risk users or require secure authentication based on risk levels.
 [community....eworks.com]

Key Risk Policies:
✔ User Risk Policy
If Microsoft believes the account is compromised →
→ Block access OR require password reset.
✔ Sign-in Risk Policy
If a suspicious sign-in is detected →
→ Require MFA OR block login.
✔ MFA Registration Policy
Force users to register MFA during high-risk scenarios.
These policies are adaptive and continuously updated.

